---
description: Require local-time timestamps in agent progress updates
alwaysApply: true
---

# Timestamped Progress Updates

- Include a local-time timestamp prefix in every progress update message sent while working.
- Use this format:
  - `[HH:MM:SS] Started: <step>`
  - `[HH:MM:SS] Update: <status>`
  - `[HH:MM:SS] Completed: <step> (elapsed: <duration>)`
- For long-running commands or waits, post periodic updates with elapsed time, for example:
  - `[HH:MM:SS] Still running: <step> (elapsed: <duration>)`
- Keep final answers concise, but include timestamps in intermediary execution updates.
